{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":227234,"duration_api_ms":202226,"num_turns":43,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"4a8017f2-d239-4890-beb9-a4fd451132eb","total_cost_usd":1.679065,"usage":{"input_tokens":41,"cache_creation_input_tokens":62414,"cache_read_input_tokens":2222745,"output_tokens":7096,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":62414,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":41,"outputTokens":7096,"cacheReadInputTokens":2222745,"cacheCreationInputTokens":62414,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.679065,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"snapshot_plan_hash() silently swallows I/O errors (corrupt snapshot JSON, permission failures) via .ok(), making them indistinguishable from 'no snapshot exists.' Consider logging a warning or tracing event when read_snapshot returns an Err that is not NotFound, so operators can detect a corrupted snapshot that is silently preventing plan_hash auto-population.","rationale":"A corrupt snapshot file would cause plan_hash to silently remain None on every new task run entry, with no signal in logs. This is a degraded-data-quality issue rather than a correctness bug, but it undermines the goal of Issue 3 (lineage should not lose plan linkage) because the system would fail to auto-populate without any indication of why."},{"body":"The deny_unknown_fields guard on StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails provides runtime detection (parse returns None, which causes journal repair to fall back to appending), but the stated acceptance criterion asks for 'compile-time or test failure.' The round-trip tests fulfill the 'test failure' criterion only if they are run — consider adding a doc-comment or CLAUDE.md note explaining that the deny_unknown_fields + round-trip test pair is the chosen enforcement mechanism, so future developers know this is an intentional two-layer guard rather than just a serde annotation.","rationale":"Without this documentation, a future developer who adds a field to the model's payload struct but forgets to run tests could ship silently drifted structs. The deny_unknown_fields provides a runtime safety net (parse fails, repair skips), but the stated goal is compile-time or test detection. Making the enforcement strategy explicit reduces the chance of someone relying on only one layer."}],"summary":"Reviewed all changes across src/adapters/fs.rs and src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs. The implementation correctly addresses all three issues: (1) deny_unknown_fields + round-trip tests catch journal struct drift, (2) runless-to-named completion now accepts when started_at matches and rejects on mismatch, (3) plan_hash auto-population from snapshot only on new entry creation, with intentional skip on existing row backfill/finalization to prevent plan-evolution mislabeling. All 1163 tests pass. Test coverage is thorough, including plan-evolution edge cases, legacy-row preservation, and terminal replay safety. Two minor suggestions: snapshot_plan_hash silently swallows non-NotFound I/O errors, and the enforcement strategy for struct sync could be documented more explicitly."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"cd5a46b9-3e55-4657-88e5-90f6708f3514"}
